                  <additions ana="medium">
                     <p>Along with the manuscript is a double folio in the hand of <name type="person" key="JonTho010">Jóns Þorkelssonar</name>, with information
                        about the manucript's origin as well as a list of contents. Kom 4.11.1896 frá Daða
                           Daviðssyni á Kötlustöðum í Vatnsdal, fyrir milligöngu Björns
                           alþingismanns Sigfússonar í Grímstungum</p>
                     <p>Both the P.E.Ó.-catalogue and Jón Þorkelsson consider the scribe to be <name type="person" key="JonJon047">Jónas Jónsson</name> á
                           <placeName>Stóra-Vatnshorni</placeName>. Kristinn Kristjánsson, in a
                        thesis 1979 states that the scribe is <name type="person" key="JohJon004">Jóhannes Jónsson</name> (1798-1877), Jóhannes the blind, a farmhand at
                           <placeName>Stóra-Vatnshorni</placeName>, later a farmer at
                           <placeName>Smyrlahóll</placeName>
                     </p>
                     <p>On ffl2r-ffl2v there is a later table of contents</p>
                  </additions>
